{"parentUuid":"fa81a49b-b772-4aac-a8f1-31c45fc0ff56","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a043ee07da5273413","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccw1jW5ZYfNGwWqv6KWjm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017Z3zD92XvH6hhcaNCWYedu","name":"Read","input":{"file_path":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/security-report.md"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9449,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9449,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":5,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccw1jVGSqNkLG3woRtuVS","attributionAgent":"debugging","type":"assistant","uuid":"d4ee78ef-3066-45ff-8d55-6db21308747c","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:53:47.947Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"d4ee78ef-3066-45ff-8d55-6db21308747c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3ec49c5b-ea47-4406-aa22-ead73596f6c4","agentId":"a043ee07da5273413","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017Z3zD92XvH6hhcaNCWYedu","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstatus: issues-found\n3\tran_at: 2026-07-11T21:30:09Z\n4\tscope: diff\n5\tsince_commit: 791a37c903a0420cfa81ec90e35cdbfe74dc9443\n6\tcritical_count: 1\n7\twarning_count: 0\n8\tfixed_count: 0\n9\ttotal_findings: 2\n10\tsemgrep_findings: 0\n11\tosv_findings: 0\n12\tcheckov_findings: null\n13\ttrivy_findings: null\n14\tstride_mechanisms_verified: 7\n15\tstride_mechanisms_missing: 1\n16\tstride_new_threats: 0\n17\t---\n18\t\n19\t# Security report — `usage-daily` (`GET /v1/usage/daily`)\n20\t\n21\tScope: working-tree change set since `791a37c` (diff-scoping-conventions). Additive\n22\tcustomer-scoped read endpoint. Files scanned:\n23\t\n24\t- NEW: `src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`, `src/services/usage_daily_service.py`,\n25\t  `src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`, `tests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py`,\n26\t  `tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py`\n27\t- MODIFIED (additive): `src/main.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`\n28\t\n29\t## Bottom line\n30\t\n31\tThe new endpoint's own code is clean: SQL is fully parameterized/bound, the `date` input\n32\tis validated by an anchored ReDoS-safe allowlist, the tenant predicate is `api_key_id`-first\n33\tfrom the authenticated principal, errors fail closed, and no secrets/new dependencies were\n34\tintroduced. **One blocking critical remains** — the RLS backstop the plan names as a\n35\tdefense-in-depth control for the IDOR threat is **inert for the application role** (a\n36\tpre-existing migration-0002 gap). The primary app-level tenant predicate is present and\n37\tcorrect, so the endpoint is **not independently exploitable** for cross-tenant reads, but\n38\tper the presence-is-not-efficacy rule (U-02) a named-but-inert security mechanism is a\n39\tcritical and is routed to remediation.\n40\t\n41\t## Tools run\n42\t\n43\t| Tool | Result | Notes |\n44\t|---|---|---|\n45\t| Semgrep (native 1.169.0, `p/secrets` + `p/owasp-top-ten` + `p/python` + `p/default`, 1145 rules) | 0 findings | Scanned exactly the 5 change-set code files; clean. The Docker wrapper could not run — its container cannot resolve `semgrep.dev` (offline registry). Ran the **native** binary instead (host resolves fine). `.pipeline/semgrep.json`. |\n46\t| OSV Scanner | 0 unfiltered (1 filtered/waived) | Scanned `poetry.lock` (80 pkgs). Only finding = `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest 8.3.4, CVSS 6.8 Medium, dev-only), **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` (below the 7.0 gate floor; not in the deployed surface). No new dependency introduced by this feature. `.pipeline/osv.json`. |\n47\t| Gitleaks | 0 in change-set | 128 tree-wide hits, all in `.venv/` (vendored botocore data), `.pipeline/archive/`, `docs/`, and pre-existing test fixtures (`test_schemas_events.py`, `test_usage_export_endpoint.py`) — **none** in any change-set file. `.pipeline/gitleaks.json`. |\n48\t| lockfile-check (supply-chain) | clean | No manifest/lockfile drift; no unpinned specifiers. |\n49\t| asvs-sast (Tier-1) | 0 critical, 0 warning | No JWT-none / fast-hash / non-CSPRNG / weak-cipher in the diff. |\n50\t| ast-grep (structural, advisory-only) | 1 hit, pre-existing | See \"ast-grep\" below. |\n51\t| Trivy fs / config | skipped (disclosed) | Docker DNS unreachable (`mirror.gcr.io`) — vuln DB pull failed. Not a required scanner (no Dockerfile in change-set); OSV covered SCA. |\n52\t| Checkov | not run (n/a) | No `infra/` change in the change-set. |\n53\t\n54\t## Complete findings inventory\n55\t\n56\t| # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |\n57\t|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n58\t| 1 | manual-6d | STRIDE-efficacy: `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS backstop inert for app role (owner, no FORCE) | critical (per U-02) | no (primary app predicate present; no object-id input) | `alembic/versions/0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py:67-73` (+ runtime owner in `src/db/session.py`) | could-not-remediate |\n59\t| 2 | osv | GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g (PYSEC-2026-1845, pytest 8.3.4) | medium (CVSS 6.8) | no (dev-only, not in prod container) | `poetry.lock` | reported-only (waived, `osv-scanner.toml`) |\n60\t\n61\t`total_findings = 2`. Semgrep, gitleaks (in-scope), lockfile-check, asvs-sast, and manual\n62\tchecks 6a/6c/6e/6f/6g each produced **0** findings, so contribute no rows.\n63\t\n64\t## Critical finding detail (row 1)\n65\t\n66\t**STRIDE mitigation ineffective — RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`.**\n67\t\n68\tThe plan's Information-Disclosure (IDOR) mitigation claims: *\"plus RLS policy\n69\t`usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` (migration 0002) **enforced** via `SET LOCAL\n70\tapp.current_api_key_id`.\"* That claim is false for the application role:\n71\t\n72\t- Migration `0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py` runs `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup ENABLE\n73\t  ROW LEVEL SECURITY` and `CREATE POLICY usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` but **does not**\n74\t  run `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`.\n75\t- Migrations execute as `meterly_app` (per `0003`'s own comment: the migration job resolves\n76\t  the DB URL through the same secrets facade the app uses → the `meterly_app` credential),\n77\t  so `meterly_app` **owns** `usage_rollup`. The runtime app also connects as `meterly_app`.\n78\t- In PostgreSQL, a **table owner bypasses non-FORCE RLS** regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS`. So\n79\t  the policy is inert for the app role — the backstop does not fire.\n80\t- This is confirmed by the codebase's own intent: migration `0003` applies `ALTER TABLE\n81\t  quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` with a comment documenting exactly this owner-bypass\n82\t  semantics. `0001` (events) and `0002` (usage_rollup) omit it — an inconsistency/oversight,\n83\t  not a deliberate exception.\n84\t\n85\t**Why it is not independently exploitable through this feature:** the primary tenant control\n86\tis present and correct — `aggregate_daily_event_counts` (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`)\n87\tuses `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` as its **first** predicate, bound from\n88\t`principal.api_key_id` (never client input), and the endpoint accepts **no** `customer_id` /\n89\t`api_key_id` parameter (`extra=\"forbid\"`), so there is no IDOR selector. Cross-tenant reads\n90\tare blocked at the application layer today. The finding is that the *defense-in-depth\n91\tbackstop* — the layer meant to catch a future missing-predicate bug — is silently disabled.\n92\t\n93\t**Verified-safe remediation (for the remediation/debugging role):** add a new forward\n94\tmigration `alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`:\n95\t- upgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`\n96\t- downgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup NO FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`\n97\t- `down_revision` chained to `0003`.\n98\t\n99\tThis is **behavior-preserving**: I verified that **every runtime reader/writer of\n100\t`usage_rollup` executes inside `scoped_transaction`** (which sets `app.current_api_key_id`\n101\tvia `SET LOCAL`) — the four services `usage_daily`, `usage_export`, `quota`\n102\t(`read_tenant_quota_state_locked`), and `events` (the rollup increment) all do. Under FORCE\n103\teach still sees exactly the rows the app predicate already returns, so no legitimate query\n104\tresult changes. (The 0002 backfill `INSERT…SELECT` ran as owner without the GUC, but that\n105\tcompletes before 0004 enables FORCE, so it is unaffected.) The migration should ship with a\n106\tfails-before/passes-after tenant-isolation test proving a query with the GUC unset returns\n107\tzero rows — which is why this is routed to the remediation role (schema change + test)\n108\trather than patched inline by the security stage, consistent with how gating dependency\n109\tbumps are routed (U-19/D2).\n110\t\n111\t**Related observation (out of change-set scope, not counted):** migration `0001` gives the\n112\t`events` table the same latent gap (ENABLE without FORCE, owner = app role). The FORCE\n113\tmigration should cover `events` too for consistency; flagged here for the remediation role's\n114\tawareness though `events` is outside this feature's surface.\n115\t\n116\t## Fixes applied\n117\t\n118\tNone. The new endpoint code required no changes (clean). The single critical is a\n119\tschema-migration remediation routed to the remediation/debugging role (see above), so\n120\t`fixed_count = 0`.\n121\t\n122\t## Could not remediate — human/remediation review required\n123\t\n124\t- **Row 1 (RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`).** Requires a new alembic migration +\n125\t  isolation test; routed to the remediation role. Exact verified-safe recipe above.\n126\t\n127\t## Action required\n128\t\n129\t- **OSV `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest → 9.0.3).** Below the CVSS 7.0 gate floor (6.8),\n130\t  dev-only, and **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` with a review date\n131\t  (`ignoreUntil = 2026-10-09`). No action this cycle; the major-version bump (pytest 8→9)\n132\t  is tracked as a deliberate dev-dependency upgrade. Not introduced by this feature.\n133\t\n134\t## STRIDE mechanism verification (6d)\n135\t\n136\t8 named threats in `plan.md`; 7 mechanisms present-and-effective, 1 present-but-inert.\n137\t\n138\t| Threat | Mechanism | Evidence | Status |\n139\t|---|---|---|---|\n140\t| Spoofing (auth) | `require_api_key` composed in `_require_authenticated_and_throttled` | `routes/usage_daily.py:23-30,36` | ✓ effective |\n141\t| Tampering (`date` injection) | anchored `^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$` + `date.fromisoformat` + `[now-90d,now+1d]` → 400; value never reaches SQL as text (bound `:day_start/:day_end`) | `schemas/usage_daily.py:24,80-102`; `usage_repo.py:229-243` | ✓ effective |\n142\t| Tampering (param smuggling) | `DailyUsageQueryParams(extra=\"forbid\")` | `schemas/usage_daily.py:44,46` | ✓ effective |\n143\t| Repudiation | `logger.info(\"usage.daily.read\", …)` (no values, only counts) | `usage_daily_service.py:46-53` | ✓ effective |\n144\t| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — primary | `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` first predicate, from principal; no object-id input | `usage_repo.py:236`; `routes/usage_daily.py` | ✓ effective |\n145\t| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — backstop | `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS via `SET LOCAL` | migration `0002:67-73` | ✗ **inert (owner, no FORCE)** — row 1 |\n146\t| Info Disclosure (error leak) | central `handle_unexpected_error` generic 500; service adds no try/except; `DailyUsageResponse(extra=\"forbid\")` | `api/errors.py:97-116`; `usage_daily_service.py`; `schemas/usage_daily.py:119-122` | ✓ effective |\n147\t| DoS | Tier-2 `enforce_tier2_rate_limit` (redis token bucket, principal-keyed post-auth) + Tier-1 edge + date bound + single-day GROUP BY | `auth/rate_limit.py:136`; `routes/usage_daily.py:29` | ✓ effective |\n148\t| EoP | `require_api_key` only, no admin gate needed, no object-id → no pivot | `routes/usage_daily.py:36` | ✓ effective |\n149\t\n150\tEfficacy answers (U-02): topology — Tier-2 runs **after** auth so it is principal-keyed not\n151\tIP-keyed (✓); DB privilege — RLS owner check → **inert without FORCE** (✗, the critical);\n152\tasync runtime — no CPU-hard/blocking sync calls in the async handlers (✓); contract drift —\n153\terror scrubber owns every error body, log facade strips control chars (✓).\n154\t\n155\t## STRIDE delta / attack-surface reconciliation (6f)\n156\t\n157\t`stride_new_threats: 0`. New surface introduced by the diff = the `GET /v1/usage/daily`\n158\troute, the `aggregate_daily_event_counts` read query, and the `usage.daily.read` log event.\n159\tEvery one is covered by an existing `plan.md` threat-model entry (verified against\n160\t`surface-delta.md`, which matched the diff). No new outbound calls, subprocess, SSRF sink,\n161\tstored data, or privilege surface. No uncovered surface → no addendum entries. (The RLS\n162\tinefficacy is an *efficacy* finding on an existing mitigation, 6d, not a new-surface gap.)\n163\t\n164\t## ast-grep (structural, advisory-only — not counted)\n165\t\n166\tRan the SQL/async structural checks (F-M4-5 trigger: diff touches SQL + async entrypoints).\n167\tOne hit: `text(f\"…\")` at `usage_repo.py:134` — this is `count_usage_rollups`, a\n168\t**pre-existing, byte-for-byte-unchanged** function (diff hunks are lines 1-5 and 198-248\n169\tonly), already triaged with a `nosemgrep` pragma and a fixed-literal (non-client) WHERE\n170\tclause. The **new** `aggregate_daily_event_counts` uses a plain bound-param `text(\"\"\"…\"\"\")`\n171\twith no interpolation — clean. No blocking-call/KDF-on-event-loop hits. Advisory only; feeds\n172\tno count.\n173\t\n174\t## ASVS 5.0.0 (6g)\n175\t\n176\tTriggered chapters (from plan `## ASVS Compliance`): V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V11, V13, V16.\n177\tL1/L2 verified universally; no new in-scope L3 (reused Argon2id path's 11.2.4 already met).\n178\t\n179\t- V1 (parameterized SQL): bound params, no interpolation of caller input — met.\n180\t- V2 (validation + anti-automation): `parse_daily_date` allowlist + Tier-1/Tier-2 throttle — met.\n181\t- V6 (auth): `require_api_key` reused — met.\n182\t- V8 (8.2.2 object-level authz / tenant isolation): met **at the application layer** by the\n183\t  `api_key_id`-first predicate + no object-id input. The RLS defense-in-depth backstop is\n184\t  degraded (row 1) — surfaced once as the 6d critical, not double-counted here.\n185\t- V11 (crypto): reused Argon2id key verification — met.\n186\t- V13 (config / least-privilege): app role `NOBYPASSRLS` (infra) — met; the FORCE gap is the\n187\t  6d finding.\n188\t- V16 (logging & error handling): structured `usage.daily.read`, no PII/values/raw body;\n189\t  fail-closed central error envelope — met.\n190\t\n191\t`asvs.reconciled: true` — no unmet/unwaived code/config L1/L2 or in-scope-L3 item (the ASVS\n192\tobject-authz requirement is satisfied by the present primary control; the inert RLS backstop\n193\tis captured as the 6d critical that already flips `status` to issues-found).\n194\t\n195\t## Input / data surface reconciliation\n196\t\n197\t- **input_surface** — 1 implemented source (`GET /v1/usage/daily?date=…`), with BOTH a\n198\t  validation contract (`DailyUsageQueryParams` + `parse_daily_date`, acceptance AC3-6) AND a\n199\t  rate-limit policy (Tier-2 principal-keyed + Tier-1, acceptance AC13). `uncontrolled: []`,\n200\t  reconciled.\n201\t- **data_surface** — pure read; the diff stores no new field/table/column/cache/blob.\n202\t  `classified: 0`, `unprotected: []`, reconciled. (`data-protection-conventions` not\n203\t  triggered — `usage_rollup` was classified non-sensitive operational metering data by the\n204\t  prior feature.)\n205\t"}]},"uuid":"652aa529-e5ef-4b30-9fc7-7a87e10da1f6","timestamp":"2026-07-11T21:53:47.991Z","toolUseResult":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/security-report.md","content":"---\nstatus: issues-found\nran_at: 2026-07-11T21:30:09Z\nscope: diff\nsince_commit: 791a37c903a0420cfa81ec90e35cdbfe74dc9443\ncritical_count: 1\nwarning_count: 0\nfixed_count: 0\ntotal_findings: 2\nsemgrep_findings: 0\nosv_findings: 0\ncheckov_findings: null\ntrivy_findings: null\nstride_mechanisms_verified: 7\nstride_mechanisms_missing: 1\nstride_new_threats: 0\n---\n\n# Security report — `usage-daily` (`GET /v1/usage/daily`)\n\nScope: working-tree change set since `791a37c` (diff-scoping-conventions). Additive\ncustomer-scoped read endpoint. Files scanned:\n\n- NEW: `src/api/schemas/usage_daily.py`, `src/services/usage_daily_service.py`,\n  `src/api/routes/usage_daily.py`, `tests/integration/test_usage_daily_endpoint.py`,\n  `tests/test_schemas_usage_daily.py`\n- MODIFIED (additive): `src/main.py`, `src/repositories/usage_repo.py`\n\n## Bottom line\n\nThe new endpoint's own code is clean: SQL is fully parameterized/bound, the `date` input\nis validated by an anchored ReDoS-safe allowlist, the tenant predicate is `api_key_id`-first\nfrom the authenticated principal, errors fail closed, and no secrets/new dependencies were\nintroduced. **One blocking critical remains** — the RLS backstop the plan names as a\ndefense-in-depth control for the IDOR threat is **inert for the application role** (a\npre-existing migration-0002 gap). The primary app-level tenant predicate is present and\ncorrect, so the endpoint is **not independently exploitable** for cross-tenant reads, but\nper the presence-is-not-efficacy rule (U-02) a named-but-inert security mechanism is a\ncritical and is routed to remediation.\n\n## Tools run\n\n| Tool | Result | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| Semgrep (native 1.169.0, `p/secrets` + `p/owasp-top-ten` + `p/python` + `p/default`, 1145 rules) | 0 findings | Scanned exactly the 5 change-set code files; clean. The Docker wrapper could not run — its container cannot resolve `semgrep.dev` (offline registry). Ran the **native** binary instead (host resolves fine). `.pipeline/semgrep.json`. |\n| OSV Scanner | 0 unfiltered (1 filtered/waived) | Scanned `poetry.lock` (80 pkgs). Only finding = `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest 8.3.4, CVSS 6.8 Medium, dev-only), **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` (below the 7.0 gate floor; not in the deployed surface). No new dependency introduced by this feature. `.pipeline/osv.json`. |\n| Gitleaks | 0 in change-set | 128 tree-wide hits, all in `.venv/` (vendored botocore data), `.pipeline/archive/`, `docs/`, and pre-existing test fixtures (`test_schemas_events.py`, `test_usage_export_endpoint.py`) — **none** in any change-set file. `.pipeline/gitleaks.json`. |\n| lockfile-check (supply-chain) | clean | No manifest/lockfile drift; no unpinned specifiers. |\n| asvs-sast (Tier-1) | 0 critical, 0 warning | No JWT-none / fast-hash / non-CSPRNG / weak-cipher in the diff. |\n| ast-grep (structural, advisory-only) | 1 hit, pre-existing | See \"ast-grep\" below. |\n| Trivy fs / config | skipped (disclosed) | Docker DNS unreachable (`mirror.gcr.io`) — vuln DB pull failed. Not a required scanner (no Dockerfile in change-set); OSV covered SCA. |\n| Checkov | not run (n/a) | No `infra/` change in the change-set. |\n\n## Complete findings inventory\n\n| # | source | id | severity | exploitable | location | disposition |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| 1 | manual-6d | STRIDE-efficacy: `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS backstop inert for app role (owner, no FORCE) | critical (per U-02) | no (primary app predicate present; no object-id input) | `alembic/versions/0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py:67-73` (+ runtime owner in `src/db/session.py`) | could-not-remediate |\n| 2 | osv | GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g (PYSEC-2026-1845, pytest 8.3.4) | medium (CVSS 6.8) | no (dev-only, not in prod container) | `poetry.lock` | reported-only (waived, `osv-scanner.toml`) |\n\n`total_findings = 2`. Semgrep, gitleaks (in-scope), lockfile-check, asvs-sast, and manual\nchecks 6a/6c/6e/6f/6g each produced **0** findings, so contribute no rows.\n\n## Critical finding detail (row 1)\n\n**STRIDE mitigation ineffective — RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`.**\n\nThe plan's Information-Disclosure (IDOR) mitigation claims: *\"plus RLS policy\n`usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` (migration 0002) **enforced** via `SET LOCAL\napp.current_api_key_id`.\"* That claim is false for the application role:\n\n- Migration `0002_create_usage_rollup_backfill.py` runs `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup ENABLE\n  ROW LEVEL SECURITY` and `CREATE POLICY usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` but **does not**\n  run `FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`.\n- Migrations execute as `meterly_app` (per `0003`'s own comment: the migration job resolves\n  the DB URL through the same secrets facade the app uses → the `meterly_app` credential),\n  so `meterly_app` **owns** `usage_rollup`. The runtime app also connects as `meterly_app`.\n- In PostgreSQL, a **table owner bypasses non-FORCE RLS** regardless of `NOBYPASSRLS`. So\n  the policy is inert for the app role — the backstop does not fire.\n- This is confirmed by the codebase's own intent: migration `0003` applies `ALTER TABLE\n  quotas FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` with a comment documenting exactly this owner-bypass\n  semantics. `0001` (events) and `0002` (usage_rollup) omit it — an inconsistency/oversight,\n  not a deliberate exception.\n\n**Why it is not independently exploitable through this feature:** the primary tenant control\nis present and correct — `aggregate_daily_event_counts` (`src/repositories/usage_repo.py`)\nuses `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` as its **first** predicate, bound from\n`principal.api_key_id` (never client input), and the endpoint accepts **no** `customer_id` /\n`api_key_id` parameter (`extra=\"forbid\"`), so there is no IDOR selector. Cross-tenant reads\nare blocked at the application layer today. The finding is that the *defense-in-depth\nbackstop* — the layer meant to catch a future missing-predicate bug — is silently disabled.\n\n**Verified-safe remediation (for the remediation/debugging role):** add a new forward\nmigration `alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py`:\n- upgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`\n- downgrade: `op.execute(\"ALTER TABLE usage_rollup NO FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY\")`\n- `down_revision` chained to `0003`.\n\nThis is **behavior-preserving**: I verified that **every runtime reader/writer of\n`usage_rollup` executes inside `scoped_transaction`** (which sets `app.current_api_key_id`\nvia `SET LOCAL`) — the four services `usage_daily`, `usage_export`, `quota`\n(`read_tenant_quota_state_locked`), and `events` (the rollup increment) all do. Under FORCE\neach still sees exactly the rows the app predicate already returns, so no legitimate query\nresult changes. (The 0002 backfill `INSERT…SELECT` ran as owner without the GUC, but that\ncompletes before 0004 enables FORCE, so it is unaffected.) The migration should ship with a\nfails-before/passes-after tenant-isolation test proving a query with the GUC unset returns\nzero rows — which is why this is routed to the remediation role (schema change + test)\nrather than patched inline by the security stage, consistent with how gating dependency\nbumps are routed (U-19/D2).\n\n**Related observation (out of change-set scope, not counted):** migration `0001` gives the\n`events` table the same latent gap (ENABLE without FORCE, owner = app role). The FORCE\nmigration should cover `events` too for consistency; flagged here for the remediation role's\nawareness though `events` is outside this feature's surface.\n\n## Fixes applied\n\nNone. The new endpoint code required no changes (clean). The single critical is a\nschema-migration remediation routed to the remediation/debugging role (see above), so\n`fixed_count = 0`.\n\n## Could not remediate — human/remediation review required\n\n- **Row 1 (RLS backstop inert on `usage_rollup`).** Requires a new alembic migration +\n  isolation test; routed to the remediation role. Exact verified-safe recipe above.\n\n## Action required\n\n- **OSV `GHSA-6w46-j5rx-g56g` (pytest → 9.0.3).** Below the CVSS 7.0 gate floor (6.8),\n  dev-only, and **waived** in the committed `osv-scanner.toml` with a review date\n  (`ignoreUntil = 2026-10-09`). No action this cycle; the major-version bump (pytest 8→9)\n  is tracked as a deliberate dev-dependency upgrade. Not introduced by this feature.\n\n## STRIDE mechanism verification (6d)\n\n8 named threats in `plan.md`; 7 mechanisms present-and-effective, 1 present-but-inert.\n\n| Threat | Mechanism | Evidence | Status |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Spoofing (auth) | `require_api_key` composed in `_require_authenticated_and_throttled` | `routes/usage_daily.py:23-30,36` | ✓ effective |\n| Tampering (`date` injection) | anchored `^\\d{4}-\\d{2}-\\d{2}$` + `date.fromisoformat` + `[now-90d,now+1d]` → 400; value never reaches SQL as text (bound `:day_start/:day_end`) | `schemas/usage_daily.py:24,80-102`; `usage_repo.py:229-243` | ✓ effective |\n| Tampering (param smuggling) | `DailyUsageQueryParams(extra=\"forbid\")` | `schemas/usage_daily.py:44,46` | ✓ effective |\n| Repudiation | `logger.info(\"usage.daily.read\", …)` (no values, only counts) | `usage_daily_service.py:46-53` | ✓ effective |\n| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — primary | `WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id` first predicate, from principal; no object-id input | `usage_repo.py:236`; `routes/usage_daily.py` | ✓ effective |\n| Info Disclosure (IDOR) — backstop | `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS via `SET LOCAL` | migration `0002:67-73` | ✗ **inert (owner, no FORCE)** — row 1 |\n| Info Disclosure (error leak) | central `handle_unexpected_error` generic 500; service adds no try/except; `DailyUsageResponse(extra=\"forbid\")` | `api/errors.py:97-116`; `usage_daily_service.py`; `schemas/usage_daily.py:119-122` | ✓ effective |\n| DoS | Tier-2 `enforce_tier2_rate_limit` (redis token bucket, principal-keyed post-auth) + Tier-1 edge + date bound + single-day GROUP BY | `auth/rate_limit.py:136`; `routes/usage_daily.py:29` | ✓ effective |\n| EoP | `require_api_key` only, no admin gate needed, no object-id → no pivot | `routes/usage_daily.py:36` | ✓ effective |\n\nEfficacy answers (U-02): topology — Tier-2 runs **after** auth so it is principal-keyed not\nIP-keyed (✓); DB privilege — RLS owner check → **inert without FORCE** (✗, the critical);\nasync runtime — no CPU-hard/blocking sync calls in the async handlers (✓); contract drift —\nerror scrubber owns every error body, log facade strips control chars (✓).\n\n## STRIDE delta / attack-surface reconciliation (6f)\n\n`stride_new_threats: 0`. New surface introduced by the diff = the `GET /v1/usage/daily`\nroute, the `aggregate_daily_event_counts` read query, and the `usage.daily.read` log event.\nEvery one is covered by an existing `plan.md` threat-model entry (verified against\n`surface-delta.md`, which matched the diff). No new outbound calls, subprocess, SSRF sink,\nstored data, or privilege surface. No uncovered surface → no addendum entries. (The RLS\ninefficacy is an *efficacy* finding on an existing mitigation, 6d, not a new-surface gap.)\n\n## ast-grep (structural, advisory-only — not counted)\n\nRan the SQL/async structural checks (F-M4-5 trigger: diff touches SQL + async entrypoints).\nOne hit: `text(f\"…\")` at `usage_repo.py:134` — this is `count_usage_rollups`, a\n**pre-existing, byte-for-byte-unchanged** function (diff hunks are lines 1-5 and 198-248\nonly), already triaged with a `nosemgrep` pragma and a fixed-literal (non-client) WHERE\nclause. The **new** `aggregate_daily_event_counts` uses a plain bound-param `text(\"\"\"…\"\"\")`\nwith no interpolation — clean. No blocking-call/KDF-on-event-loop hits. Advisory only; feeds\nno count.\n\n## ASVS 5.0.0 (6g)\n\nTriggered chapters (from plan `## ASVS Compliance`): V1, V2, V4, V6, V8, V11, V13, V16.\nL1/L2 verified universally; no new in-scope L3 (reused Argon2id path's 11.2.4 already met).\n\n- V1 (parameterized SQL): bound params, no interpolation of caller input — met.\n- V2 (validation + anti-automation): `parse_daily_date` allowlist + Tier-1/Tier-2 throttle — met.\n- V6 (auth): `require_api_key` reused — met.\n- V8 (8.2.2 object-level authz / tenant isolation): met **at the application layer** by the\n  `api_key_id`-first predicate + no object-id input. The RLS defense-in-depth backstop is\n  degraded (row 1) — surfaced once as the 6d critical, not double-counted here.\n- V11 (crypto): reused Argon2id key verification — met.\n- V13 (config / least-privilege): app role `NOBYPASSRLS` (infra) — met; the FORCE gap is the\n  6d finding.\n- V16 (logging & error handling): structured `usage.daily.read`, no PII/values/raw body;\n  fail-closed central error envelope — met.\n\n`asvs.reconciled: true` — no unmet/unwaived code/config L1/L2 or in-scope-L3 item (the ASVS\nobject-authz requirement is satisfied by the present primary control; the inert RLS backstop\nis captured as the 6d critical that already flips `status` to issues-found).\n\n## Input / data surface reconciliation\n\n- **input_surface** — 1 implemented source (`GET /v1/usage/daily?date=…`), with BOTH a\n  validation contract (`DailyUsageQueryParams` + `parse_daily_date`, acceptance AC3-6) AND a\n  rate-limit policy (Tier-2 principal-keyed + Tier-1, acceptance AC13). `uncontrolled: []`,\n  reconciled.\n- **data_surface** — pure read; the diff stores no new field/table/column/cache/blob.\n  `classified: 0`, `unprotected: []`, reconciled. (`data-protection-conventions` not\n  triggered — `usage_rollup` was classified non-sensitive operational metering data by the\n  prior feature.)\n","numLines":205,"startLine":1,"totalLines":205}},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"d4ee78ef-3066-45ff-8d55-6db21308747c","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
