_rollups(\nsrc/services/usage_export_service.py:95:    CSV-encoded row per streamed `usage_rollup` record.\nsrc/services/usage_export_service.py:118:            async for record in stream_usage_rollups(\nsrc/services/usage_export_service.py:157:            resource=\"usage_rollup\",\nsrc/services/usage_service.py:13:from src.repositories.usage_repo import find_usage_rollup\nsrc/services/usage_service.py:31:        rollup = await find_usage_rollup(\n=== grep current_api_key_id / SET LOCAL ===\nsrc/db/README.md:23:- At the start of each transaction (entered via `async with session_context(api_key_id)`), the context manager executes `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id = :api_key_id`.\nsrc/db/README.md:25:- The `SET LOCAL` is per-transaction, so the context is automatically cleared at commit (no cleanup needed).\nsrc/db/session.py:6:transaction that sets `app.current_api_key_id` via `SET LOCAL`, which backs the\nsrc/db/session.py:61:    Sets `app.current_api_key_id` with `SET LOCAL` at the start of the\nsrc/db/session.py:77:    \"\"\"Build the `SET LOCAL` statement for the current-tenant RLS setting.\nsrc/db/session.py:79:    A separate function keeps the (slightly unusual) `set_config` call —\nsrc/db/session.py:80:    `SET LOCAL` does not accept a bound parameter directly in all drivers —\nsrc/db/session.py:85:    return text(\"SELECT set_config('app.current_api_key_id', :api_key_id, true)\")\nsrc/repositories/README.md:26:- RLS is set per-transaction by `src/db.session_context` before the first query runs (sets the `app.current_api_key_id` PostgreSQL context variable).\nsrc/repositories/README.md:58:- Before any query, `src/db.session_context` sets `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id = :id` in the transaction.\nsrc/repositories/README.md:60:- The `SET LOCAL` is per-transaction (automatically cleared at commit), so no context leakage across requests.\nsrc/services/usage_export_service.py:100:    transaction so the `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id` RLS-backstop","stderr":"