{"parentUuid":"bf2fee6a-546a-482c-b208-428f4b6964fe","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"3ec49c5b-ea47-4406-aa22-ead73596f6c4","agentId":"a043ee07da5273413","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FTRvBfthz9zHoVdXcaBmHf","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/state.json has been updated successfully. (file state is current in your context — no need to Read it back)"}]},"uuid":"174e39cf-ab5e-4bff-9d5b-7b809269b5cb","timestamp":"2026-07-11T22:53:34.758Z","toolUseResult":{"filePath":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/state.json","oldString":"  \"debug_retry_count\": {\n    \"sanity\": 0,\n    \"remediation\": 0\n  },","newString":"  \"debug_retry_count\": {\n    \"sanity\": 0,\n    \"remediation\": 1\n  },","originalFile":"{\n  \"debug_retry_count\": {\n    \"sanity\": 0,\n    \"remediation\": 0\n  },\n  \"max_retries\": 3,\n  \"feature\": \"usage-daily\"\n}\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":7,"newStart":1,"newLines":7,"lines":[" {","   \"debug_retry_count\": {","     \"sanity\": 0,","-    \"remediation\": 0","+    \"remediation\": 1","   },","   \"max_retries\": 3,","   \"feature\": \"usage-daily\""]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"bf2fee6a-546a-482c-b208-428f4b6964fe","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
{"parentUuid":"174e39cf-ab5e-4bff-9d5b-7b809269b5cb","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a043ee07da5273413","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011Ccw6JEc2bDFttjHUnW2kd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The remediation is complete. Here is the summary.\n\n## What the finding was\nThe security stage flagged one CRITICAL (U-02, presence ≠ efficacy): the `usage_rollup_tenant_isolation` RLS policy is named in the STRIDE model as the enforced defense-in-depth backstop for the IDOR threat on `GET /v1/usage/daily`, but it was **inert**. Migration `0002` ran `ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY` without `FORCE`, and the app connects as the table owner (`meterly_app`) — a PostgreSQL owner bypasses non-FORCE RLS, so the policy never constrained the app's queries.\n\n## Reproduced first\nI authored the DB-layer regression test and ran it against the then-head `0003` (no FORCE). It connects as a non-superuser **owner** of `usage_rollup` (the production `meterly_app` role class — the only role whose visibility flips on `FORCE`; a NOBYPASSRLS non-owner is bound by plain `ENABLE` and can't witness the bug, and the testcontainers superuser bypasses RLS entirely). Result: with the app filter absent, the owner saw **both** tenants' rows, and saw all rows even with the tenant GUC unset — 2 failed. That directly reproduces owner-bypass.\n\n## Fix (minimal, mirrors 0003)\n- `/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/alembic/versions/0004_force_rls_usage_rollup.py` — new migration, `down_revision` `0003`: upgrade `ALTER TABLE usage_rollup FORCE ROW LEVEL SECURITY`, downgrade `... NO FORCE ...`. Scoped to `usage_rollup` only; `events` left untouched per the out-of-scope ledger item.\n\nConfirmed behavior-preserving by code inspection: every runtime reader/writer of `usage_rollup` (`find_usage_rollup`, `count/stream_usage_rollups`, `aggregate_daily_event_counts`, `increment_usage_rollup`, and the quota path's `read_tenant_quota_state_locked`) runs inside `scoped_transaction`, which issues `SET LOCAL app.current_api_key_id`. No direct access outside it.\n\n## Proof (fails-before / passes-after)\n- Migration round-trip on a scratch Postgres: `upgrade head` sets `relforcerowsecurity=true`; `downgrade -1` clears it; re-`upgrade head` sets it again — clean both directions.\n- Regression test `/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/tests/integration/test_usage_rollup_rls_backstop.py`: 2 failed at `0003`, 2 passed at `0004`, and 8/8 all-pass on re-runs (no flakiness).\n- Full suite (`pytest -m \"not perf\" --ignore=test_perf_k6_load --cov=src --cov-branch`): 254 passed / 0 failed, branch coverage **89%** (≥85%). `import src.main` boots cleanly.\n\n## Sanctioned deviation handled\nThe usage-daily plan said \"no new migration\"; the security-critical overrides that. The quota list/delete AC14 guard `test_no_new_alembic_migration_added` (`/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/tests/integration/test_quotas_list_delete.py`) asserted exactly 3 migration files, so it failed on `0004`. I updated it to allow the sanctioned migration while preserving its real intent — verifying the only new revision performs DDL on `usage_rollup` only, never `quotas`.\n\n## Bookkeeping\n- Appended a dated root-cause/evidence/fix entry to `/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/debug-notes.md`.\n- Incremented `debug_retry_count.remediation` 0 → 1 (of 3) in `/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test/.pipeline/state.json`.\n\nNote: the k6 load module was deselected for my run (it pulls a Docker image, skips in CI, and is unaffected by this schema change). The testing agent owns full-suite validation on the post-remediation re-run. The security stage can now re-scan to confirm the critical is cleared."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":339,"cache_read_input_tokens":96721,"output_tokens":1549,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":339},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1549,"cache_read_input_tokens":96721,"cache_creation_input_tokens":339,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":339,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011Ccw6JDPMXDydvsyfRafSf","attributionAgent":"debugging","type":"assistant","uuid":"d3b835c4-90cb-4101-a512-7fdf50d80303","timestamp":"2026-07-11T22:53:53.390Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/mnt/c/Users/brett/OneDrive/Documents/GitHub/meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"8b12bd3f-3c00-43c5-ad29-92ed49e714d3","version":"2.1.207","gitBranch":"feature/usage-daily"}
